headline: GE Aerospace Wins Big United Deal And Expands Long Term Engine Base
summary: GE Aerospace, part of General Electric (NYSE:GE), has agreed to supply 300 GEnx engines to United Airlines for its Boeing 787 Dreamliner fleet. The deal secures United’s position as the largest GEnx operator worldwide and deepens GE’s role in widebody aircraft propulsion. The agreement also supports a long runway of recurring service and maintenance work tied to these engines over time. headline: Praana Group Advances Strategic Expansion with Appointment of Darpan Parikh
summary: Praana Group, a diversified conglomerate with businesses spanning specialty chemicals and fiberglass, and Galata Chemicals, a global leader in specialty additives and performance chemicals, have announced the appointment of Darpan Parikh as the Member of their Board and Chief Executive Officer of Galata Chemicals. This appointment marks an important milestone in the Group's continued evolution as a globally integrated specialty chemicals and advanced materials platform.
